description: US Secretary of State Marco Rubio said progress has been made in talks between the American and Ukrainian teams in Florida on Sunday. Donald Trump's special envoy Steve Witkoff, criticized for his close ties to Russia, is expected to present an amended draft of a peace plan to Russian leader Vladimir Putin on Monday.

Two French police officers who hit motorbike on highway go on trial
description: Two French police officers face charges of intentional violence in a Paris-region court on Monday. Le Monde has reviewed testimonies and surveillance footage of an incident in which a police vehicle came into contact with a motorcycle on a busy highway in October.

headline: Two births and 27 deaths in one village: Poland's tumbling birthrate
description: With an average of 1.03 children per woman, Poland has the lowest fertility rate in Europe. Increasing family allowances has not changed that. The exhaustion of the population following the collapse of the 1990s, and then two decades of economic boom, is one of the explanations.

headline: 2026 edition Angoulême International Comics Festival officially canceled
description: The organizers announced in a statement released on Monday a decision that had seemed inevitable since the series of withdrawals by authors, publishing houses and public funders.

headline: Louvre's former Pavillon des Sessions reopens amid turmoil
description: Renamed the Gallery of the Five Continents, the space will reopen to the public on December 3, even as the Louvre faces accusations of prioritizing high-profile renovations over security.

The last-minute fight to save Gaza's ancient archaeological treasures
description: Amid the vast destruction of the war, a small group of determined individuals fought to save Gaza's archaeological heritage. On September 10, they secured a few hours' reprieve from the Israeli army before a storage depot filled with artifacts was bombed to perform a delicate evacuation – the result of intense, high-level negotiations.

headline: Can French citizens be mobilized in the event of war?
description: Statements by General Fabien Mandon and President Emmanuel Macron's announcements about a voluntary national service have raised questions about a scenario that, until recently, seemed unimaginable.

headline: 'Dédé la Sardine' and Russian oil: Inside the affair that has haunted Total for 15 years
description: Seven people have been ordered to stand trial for their involvement in an arbitration process that was allegedly manipulated in order to extract the equivalent of €16 billion from French oil company Total. Their trial begins on Monday.
